<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-11-02T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-11-02T15:00:00-05:00" n="622" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.933/159: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-02T15:00:00-05:00">November 2, 1929—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>359. Referring to the last sentence in paragraph 3, my 354, October 28, 7
                            p.m. Please immediately reply as to what action has been or is being
                            taken.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>